transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi. I'm trying to cancel an order. I was looking at my account last night and somehow placed an order and I didn't want to.

Speaker 1: I don't know how you do that, but okay, sir. One second.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: I need your name and zip code.

Speaker 2: Arvid Johnson, A-R-V-I-D. Johnson, 5-4-8-0-1.

Speaker 1: Rocky Ridge Road, sir?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: So because this went in overnight, it was already put in the mail this morning, sir. You're going to have to return it when it arrives to you.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: So when it arrives, do a return to sender and then it'll come back to us and we'll refund you.

Speaker 2: Okay. And so am I on like a subscription now?

Speaker 1: What I'm going to do is I'm going to close your account entirely so this doesn't happen again.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: So you won't be able to order at all, but that way it won't happen anymore.

Speaker 2: I would appreciate that.

Speaker 1: Yeah. I don't know what you did, but just return it and you'll get your money back.

Speaker 2: Okay. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Thank you.
